# storysync - Storybook to Figma

Read components from Storybook MCP and write them to Figma MCP as a component library.

## Requirements

- Storybook dev server running with `@storybook/addon-mcp` >= 0.5.0 (Vite-based Storybook 9+ or 10+, Node 24+)
- Storybook MCP connected (endpoint at `/mcp` on the dev server)
- Figma MCP connected (`/add-plugin figma` or add `https://mcp.figma.com/mcp`)
- Figma Full seat (Dev seats are read-only outside drafts). Starter plans limited to 6 tool calls/month.

## Workflow

1. Call `list-all-documentation({ withStoryIds: true })` to get component IDs.
2. For each, call `get-documentation({ id: "<component-id>" })`. Parse the TypeScript `Props` type.
3. Map props: `boolean` -> Figma boolean variant. Union of string literals -> variant property. Skip everything else (strings, numbers, callbacks, ReactNode, children, className, style, ref, key, aria-*, data-*, on*).
4. Cartesian product of mapped props, capped at 256.
5. Write with `use_figma` - component name, variant properties with types/values/defaults, file key, and `skillNames: "figma-use"`.
6. Summarize: components synced, variant counts, failures, caps.
